President Obama will be participating in a national tele-town hall meeting with senior citizens to discuss the Affordable Care Act and efforts to combat senior scams and fraud. The meeting will take place at the Holiday Park Multipurpose Senior Center in Wheaton, Maryland and will also be open to seniors across the country via phone. HHS Secretary Kathleen Sebelius and representatives from various organizations will also be present. These organizations represent over 40 million seniors and will be organizing satellite town hall meetings across the country. The event will be broadcast live on C-SPAN and will be pooled press.